{"version":3,"term":{"cols":80,"rows":24},"timestamp":1783507414,"command":"bash scripts/demo_kill_resume.sh","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh"}}
[0.012, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m▸ Portage crash-recovery demo: kill the worker mid-migration, watch it resume.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.161, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✔ stack up ({\"status\":\"ok\",\"db\":\"ok\"})\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▸ 1. Submit a migration job (with a pre-test delay = our kill window)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.041, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✔ job f89ffe13 submitted\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m▸ 2. Worker ingests the repo, plans the task DAG, migrates each file with the LLM…\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[8.806, "o", "   10:43:37 INFO  [portage.agent] INGEST done nodes=32 edges=128 files=6 blast=ok\r\n   10:43:39 INFO  [portage.agent] PLAN done tasks=3 affected_tests=['tests/test_api.py'] worktree=/workspaces/f89ffe13-9f56-418c-9515-4ab11d1a89a3-migrated\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✔ checkpointed through Ingest → Plan → Execute; now inside Verify\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m▸ 3. 💀 SIGKILL the worker — mid-run, no graceful shutdown\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.175, "o", "\u001b[1;31m✖ worker is dead (job f89ffe13 was mid-flight)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.007, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m▸ 4. Restart the worker. The job lease expires; any worker can reclaim it.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.203, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✔ new worker polling\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▸ 5. Watch it RESUME from the Postgres checkpoint (not from zero)…\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[9.907, "o", "   10:43:57 INFO  [portage.agent] job=f89ffe13-9f56-418c-9515-4ab11d1a89a3 RESUME from checkpoint | next=('verify',) loaded_step_log=['ingest', 'plan', 'execute'] loaded_graph_nodes=32\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m▸ 6. Wait for the job to finish\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[32.885, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✔ status: done — full suite: 6/6\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✔ INGEST ran exactly 1 time(s): the clone + graph build were NOT repeated\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✔ Crash mid-run → resume from checkpoint → migration green. That's the durability story.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "x", "0"]
